<section id="fs-id1170326067389" class="thought-questions">
<title>Thought Questions</title>
<exercise id="fs-id1170326041835">
<problem id="fs-id1170326055299">
<para id="fs-id1170326434166">If you wanted to live where the chances of a destructive earthquake were small, would you pick a location near a fault zone, near a mid ocean ridge, near a subduction zone, or on a volcanic island such as Hawaii? What are the relative risks of earthquakes at each of these locations?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1170326035403">
<problem id="fs-id1170326461101">
<para id="fs-id1170326143833">Which type of object would likely cause more damage if it struck near an urban area: a small metallic object or a large stony/icy one?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1170326291644">
<problem id="fs-id1170323800180">
<para id="fs-id1170326143004">If all life were destroyed on Earth by a large impact, would new life eventually form to take its place? Explain how conditions would have to change for life to start again on our planet.</para>
