<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1170326133764">
<term>mass extinction</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170326066556">the sudden disappearance in the fossil record of a large number of species of life, to be replaced by fossils of new species in subsequent layers; mass extinctions are indicators of catastrophic changes in the environment, such as might be produced by a large impact on Earth</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
